ANOTHER case of avian influenza has been reported on a layer farm in Val, Standerton in Mpumalanga.The virus is the same strain as the initial case reported by the department of agriculture on a Villiers farm but the two farms are not directly linked.The farm has been placed under quarantine and 25000 of the infected birds will be culled. Eggs are not allowed to be taken out of the farm.KUTULLO MADISHA kutullom@thenewage.co.za